{
  "texts": [
    "In the present study, we collected protein chains from the Protein Data Bank (PDB) 50 using the protocols 21 to construct datasets (until 10/ 2021).",
    "The collected protein chains were clustered at 95% sequence identity.",
    "From each cluster, we selected a representative protein possessing at least one annotated function.",
    "Two benchmark datasets were created, comprising 41,896 and 20,215 protein chains (with a maximum of 1024 residues each), annotated with GO terms and EC numbers, respectively.",
    "In the benchmark of EC numbers, we extracted unique annotations from the third-/fourth-level of the proteins, forming a total of six primary catalytic reaction classes: oxidoreductase, transferase, hydrolase, lyase, isomerase, and ligase."
  ]
}